headline.main: TENNESSEE.; Polities and Political Movements in Tennessee.

docs.lead_paragraph: The candidates for Governor of Tennessee are already announced for the contest in August next, and as they are both men of political renown-both practical stump orators, and both men of political experience-the fight will be, doubtless, spirited and exciting. They will pursue the old custom of stumping the State, and the ball opens at Murfreesbore' on the 1st proxime.

headline.main: LONG ISLAND.; Mortality in Brooklyn. St. Mary's--Star of the Sea.

docs.lead_paragraph: Seventy-seven deaths are reported to the Health Officer of Brooklyn, as having occurred during the week ending April 28, from the following DISEASES.--Apoplexy, atrophy, bronchitis, carbuncle, congestion of the lunge, cyania, debility, delirium tremens, dropsy, puerperal fever, typhoid fever, heart disease, whooping cough, inflammation of the heart, inflammation of the kidneys, intemperance, old age, palsy, premature birth-19-one each.
